      "amount": "1 tablespoon",
      "notes": "For serving"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "2. Roll out bao dough to 1/4-inch thickness.",
    "3. Cut out circles using a cookie cutter or the rim of a glass.",
    "4. Place a tablespoon of smoky beef in the center of each circle.",
    "5. Top with a sprinkle of Hunan spice blend, corned beef, and green onions.",
    "6. Brush edges with sesame oil and fold bao in half to form a half-moon shape.",
    "7. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 12-15 minutes.",
    "8. Serve warm with soy sauce for dipping."
  ],
